{"type":"message","id":"5c7df571","parentId":"dcf3b162","timestamp":"2026-04-14T17:42:29.455Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me compare the current state against the baseline:\n\n**Baseline (17:23 UTC):**\n- `cron:ed2d0b5d`: done (completed normally 17:08 UTC)\n- `cron:6f3323ef`: running\n- `cron:e7885813`: running (with 2 consecutive errors)\n- Pipeline: DEGRADED\n\n**Current state (17:40 UTC):**\n- `cron:ed2d0b5d`: running (status: \"running\", session: b638fed5-1c67-4e61-b5ad-544c55f5d833) — Wait, but the last message says it sent a message to group -5163901258 at 17:35 UTC saying it \"RECOVERED\" and the cron:e7885813 is \"running\" with a new clean instance. Let me look more carefully.\n\n\nLooking at the session details, I can see the cron jobs have actually shifted since the last check — `cron:6f3323ef` is still active, while `cron:e7885813` shows as done in the baseline but is now running, and `cron:ed2d0b5d` appears to have transitioned from a completed state back to running.\n\nThere's also a subagent that's completed, which wasn't part of the original baseline tracking.\n\nLooking at the state changes more carefully: the main 5p monitor cron (ed2d0b5d) has resumed running since the last baseline recorded it as done, and the Agent Status to Lead cron (e7885813) has completed after running 157 seconds. The baseline itself was recorded at 17:23 UTC, but the actual last report shows it was sent at 17:35 UTC, so there's a timing discrepancy I need to reconcile. I need to pull the heartbeat state from the last successful 5p update at 17:35 UTC to get an accurate baseline for comparison. The current state shows cron:ed2d0b5d is now running (it was done before), and I'm checking the other session statuses like cron:e7885813 which is showing a session timestamp from earlier. Let me examine what other sessions are currently active to build out the complete picture. The Telegram group session is still running, and I'm noticing several subagents spawned by the master orchestrator cron are in various states—some completed, one still running, and at least one that failed due to a Telegram tool access issue.\n\nLooking at the baseline state from the previous check, the system was degraded with three cron jobs: the QLHV monitor had finished, but the DTLX monitor and agent status reporter were both running, with the latter having experienced two consecutive errors. Since then, the QLHV monitor appears to have resumed operation, which marks a change from its completed state.\n\nComparing the session timestamps between 17:35 and 17:40 UTC, I'm noticing a discrepancy—the session ID and message sequence numbers suggest the Telegram group session at 17:38 actually came before the 17:35 report, which doesn't align with the timeline I'd expect. The 17:35 report went to the QLHV group, while the 17:38 session belongs to a different Telegram group, so they're tracking separate monitoring tasks. The key issue is that cron:e7885813 has shifted from running to done between the baseline and current state, and I need to clarify which group each report was sent to. The 5p monitor for the QLHV group is still running normally, while the DTLX monitor is also active and the Agent Status to Lead cron has completed. Looking at the current state, the session count is down to three compared to yesterday's seven, with the same three critical cron jobs accounted for, so there's been a net reduction in zombie sessions despite some cleanup activity. e7885813 ✅ completed normally (ran ~2.6 min, 0 aborts — clean run)\n\nPipeline status improved to HEALTHY since both cron jobs are running without issues, though there are still lingering subagent failures from the DTLX and QLHV sessions that are pre-existing and unchanged. I should send a brief update to the Lead highlighting the recovery and current status.\n\nThe report shows three active cron sessions running as expected, the health status shifted to healthy after fixing the consecutive aborts, and no new blockers beyond the persistent pre-existing failures that have been there all day.","thinkingSignature":"1a3e5f666fe4541685802cbac30a7f3f3bcca114501b997fbaf4e5a00ce563f7"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_3sp4t2yeqty3_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/memory/heartbeat-state.json"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":336,"output":960,"cacheRead":14272,"cacheWrite":30825,"totalTokens":46393,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776188529689,"responseId":"062daf7210e34fb1012b52b0b808479d"}}
